Bermuda Star Line Inc said it hasleased a 23,500 ton passenger vessel from Orley Shipping CoInc, of Liberia for a term with options extending for 15 years.    The vessel, SS Liberte, will be renamed the Canadian Starand will be used for cruises to Montreal from New York,beginning in June.    Orley SHipping is partially owned by Common Brothers PLC, aU.K. maritime firm which owns 60 pct of Bermuda Star's sharesand arranged debt financing for the ship's purchase.    Orley acquired the vessel from Banstead Shipping Ltd. Termswere not disclosed. Reuter&#3;